post_text:
Fruitvale ISD was awarded the Summer Career and Technical Education Grant by TEA this year. The district received $50,000 that allowed students to participate in a hands-on, work-based learning experience in which they will ultimately construct, operate, maintain, and manage a greenhouse. Along with this amazing experience, students also earned a stipend for their hard work on the build. Not only is the district proud of this group of students‚Äô hard work, we are also excited to have a greenhouse for all grade levels and courses to use for future student learning!

A huge thank you to Mr. Valdez, Mrs. Hall, and Mr. Kroontje for helping and overseeing the project!

Check out the progress so far on the Greenhouse Project.

Both the Campus Improvement Team (CIT) and District Improvement Teams (DIT) serve important roles in the district. Campus Improvement Teams examine data throughout the year and provide input in formulating plans for the campuses. The District Improvement Team serves the same purpose at the district level. This is a great opportunity to be involved with the school. These teams require parents, community representatives, and local business representatives so this opportunity is open to community members and business representatives as well. We will be offering the availability of joining through Zoom as well. We would love to have you join!

What-A-Burger is now included on the TASB website on the list of businesses that support school districts across the state. They have provided our district with What-A-Student and What-A-Teacher programs that honor great students and teachers with a free What-A-Burger meal each month. We are thankful for their kind donations. They also give the school district great deals on meals for our staff and students when needed, and deliver them to the district as well. THANK YOU CANTON WHAT-A-BURGER!

post_text: For the football scrimmage we will allow 4 guests per athlete/manager for now to be in accordance with Governor Abbott's mandate. You must be at the gate at least 15 minutes prior to the start time of the game to have your seat reserved. Your athlete will get with one of their football coaches so that the coach can create a list of names for that athlete. When we are 14 minutes away from the start time of the scrimmage we will start allowing other guests in up to a certain capacity. We will be counting all guests that attend to ensure we are in compliance with the 50% max capacity rule. All guests must wear a mask into the stadium, when a 6 ft distance cannot be maintained in the bleachers, and while walking around the stadium. If you do not have a mask, you will not be allowed to attend. Thank you for your understanding.

The other option is to email the virtual teacher, Brittany Owens, owensb@fruitvaleisd.com before 8:30 am.

post_text:
In order to make the start of school special for the students and parents in this "new normal" we are offering photo ops for all to be able to capture a special picture. In front of the administration building there will be three different photo spots: 1) a school bus with a "Welcome Back" banner 2) a school desk with books and a chalkboard and 3) a "First Day of School" photo frame.
You may access these locations on Wednesday from 11:00am until 4:00pm and then beginning at 7:15 am on Thursday.
Please remember, if you choose to take pictures on Thursday morning, to be courteous of the drop off area and not to impede traffic flow.

Also, parents decorate your cars for the first day with chalk paint, streamers- show that Bobcat spirit the first day!

WE ARE SO EXCITED TO SEE ALL OF OUR STUDENTS!!

post_text: Hi! My name is Erin Tull. I am looking forward to working at Fruitvale ISD as an instructional coach for the 2020-2021 school year. I attended Fruitvale ISD for my entire education, graduating in 2003. After graduation from high school, I attended Texas A&M-Commerce where I received my Bachelor of Arts in English in 2006. I have been employed as a secondary English teacher for all of my professional career. I am married to Chris Tull, and we have three beautiful children- Kinsley, Hudson, and Barrett. We live in Edgewood, TX.

post_text: For our athletic home games we will allow 4 guests per athlete/manager for now to be in accordance with Governor Abbott's mandate. You must be at the gate at least 15 minutes prior to the start time of the game to have your seat reserved. Your athlete will get with their respective coach so that the coach can create a list of names for that athlete. When we are 14 minutes away from the start time of the game we will start allowing other guests in up to a certain capacity. We will be counting all guests that attend to ensure we are in compliance with the 50% max capacity rule. All guests must wear a mask to all games whether the sport is indoors or outdoors. If you do not have a mask, you will not be allowed to attend. Thank you for your understanding.

Shared below are the Fruitvale ISD School Option Documents, the Fruitvale ISD Parent Commitment Form for 2020-2021 learning pathway, and the WIFI scholarship application. We will be sending these out via school messenger email and in the mail in hopes of having most families respond quickly. This will help us plan for our start on August 13th with students.
We will also be hosting a back to school meet the teacher event that is scheduled with the teacher and parents/students individually. This will give each child and their guardians an opportunity to meet with the teacher and learn new protocols for the year. We will be screening prior to these meetings and request that everyone wear a face covering per the governor's orders. We do have these available if needed in our offices.
More information on scheduling for Meet the Teacher will be out in about two weeks...
THANK YOU FOR SUPPORTING FISD! We are excited to provide the best education for our students in 2020-2021.

post_text:
Fruitvale ISD School Board changed the school calendar for 2020-2021 based on recommended guidance from the commissioner of education. The school year we will have an early start date for staff and students, and also include bad weather/pandemic days for use if we have to be out of school prior to those days. We have 12 flex days in this calendar that students may or may not have to attend school, but the total days will be 174.
Students will also have an early release on Wednesdays at 2:00 for staff training/planning and cleaning of the facilities.
We are hopeful that we will not have to use the flex days and will be out early in May, but we are planning for the possibility of being out at times according to the recommendations of the state.

Here are the skills students missed at school for employability in 6-12 grade for March, April and May. We would like to encourage parents to work on these skills at home with students this week and over the summer months. THANK YOU FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION.
Fruitvale ISD Employability Rubric for March, April, May

VII. WORK ETHICS--March
34. Entitlement
35. Apathy vs. Empathy
36. Demonstrates Responsibility & Self Discipline
37. Demonstrates a Willingness to Learn
38. Iniates GOLDEN RULE when working with others
39. Works Progressively and Independently
40. Demonstrates Quality Customer Service Skills

VIII. RESILIENCY--April
41.Resists Giving Up
42. Accepts Changes or Modifications with Ease
43. Adapts easily to different Modes of Instruction
44. Compromises With Others
45. Accepts and Uses Feedback for Self Improvement

IX. MORAL ETHICS--May
46. Honesty
47. True North Compass
48. Integrity - Pride and Quality in Work
49. Confidentiality With Others
50. Encouraging, Developing, and Coaching other Team Members with Positive Feedback

post_text: #FISDSTEM2020 Here is an example of one students science activity for the day. Kyla found a baby bird that had fallen from a nest yesterday. Today she is going to track food and water intake as she tries to keep the baby bird alive since we were unable to return in to the nest. She is keeping a log of food, such as meal worms and baby chick feed amounts. She is also tracking water intake. When you whistle the baby opens its mouth for its mom to feed her, so that is how Kyla has figured out how to feed the baby bird. She is going to document through a log and pictures to send to her teacher or to post online as instructed. We are hoping the bird rescue will be successful. She also had an old nest from last summer that she had kept to use for the bird.

Hey Guys!! Here is a reminder of how important turning in your remote learning log is to the district:
It shows the time spent in remote instruction on grade level to the state.
It is your attendance in school.
It will help with promotion determination for students to the next grade level, we will be offering summer school virtually for those who are behind with learning or just need an extra boost.
It is how the district continues to receive state funding to provide for the kids.
If you have any questions or need an extra copy please contact your child‚Äôs teacher.
We appreciate all of the hard work parents and students are putting in to get these logs completed and turned in to the school.

üêæüíôüêæShout-Out to Senior Bobcat~ Ty Winder! üêæüíôüêæ

What are you doing after graduation?

Going to work in the oilfield.

What advice would you give to younger students OR your younger self about taking advantage of school?

DO NOT QUIT. I did and it was a big mistake. I have gone back but have had to work extremely hard and take many classes at once to catch up.

What was your best memory or memories of school?

Sports- I am really going to miss competing against others especially in football.

Send a short thank you to someone who has supported you along the way.

Thank you to Mrs. Hunt for helping me get through all those classes I needed to graduate with my class. You were wonderful to work with.

post_text: Fruitvale ISD will be serving lunches from 11:00 until 12:30 or until we run out of lunches. There is also instructional pickup if your teacher has indicated that you need to pick up work this week. We can serve our enrolled students with a parent picking up food for them with id, the enrolled student does not need to be in the vehicle. Additional children up to age 18 in the vehicle with the parent that lives in our district may also receive a meal. If they are not an enrolled student they need to be in the vehicle to pick up meals. Thank you for your understanding, we ran out of meals for our students on Thursday, and we increased production, but several picked up for students that were not in the vehicle and were not enrolled students, so today we will have to say no if they are not in the vehicle. Thanks for your understanding as we feed our kids!

What are you doing after graduation?

-After graduation I plan on attending UT Tyler or Berkley and pursuing my major in Psychology.

What advice would you give to younger students OR your younger self about taking advantage of school?

- I would use your time wisely, but always remember to have fun because it goes by so fast and you'll start to miss it even if you don't think you will.

What was your best memory or memories of school?

-My best memory was getting to see my friends everyday and having non-stops laughs at random things.

post_text:
To Whom It May Concern,



As the impact of the COVID-19 emergency continues to grow, we've begun to feel the impact in our rural areas. As new steps are taken to contain this pandemic, the ability to stay connected remotely to family, work and school becomes increasingly important.



At Peoples, we have been working together to find ways to help connect families and remote workers who are being impacted during this time. To help individuals in need of internet connectivity, we will be offering the following:

Free Setup
30 days free internet service
As always - No Data Caps and No Throttling
This service requires the installation of equipment at the customer's home and will be subject to contract terms. To determine service availability and/or sign up for service, visit peoplescom.net or call 1-800-333-9779.



Please help share this information and let's get your neighbors connected.



Thank you,

Peoples

post_text: Reminder, meals will be provided today at Fruitvale ISD from 11:00 until 12:30 or until we run out today. Teachers are going to be calling today and tomorrow and we hope to have a more accurate count of meal pickup for Thursday. We are providing all children in Fruitvale, age 0-18 meals today, if you have your ID with you you may pick up without your school children in the vehicle, but if you have a different younger child bring them through the line and we will give them a meal also. The meals picked up today will be 3 breakfast and 3 lunches, and then we will provide another pickup on Thursday for 3 breakfast and 3 lunches as well. So, students and children in our school community should have breakfast and lunch meals Monday through Saturday if you pick up on Monday and Thursdays. The line for meal pickup will be the junior high pick up line in the gate beside the high school to the back of the cafeteria and out the gate by administration. Be kind and sweet as you wait for meals:)

Practices may be held for local teams in their local districts at the district discretion, but not interschool competitions. Have a great spring break, and stay safe!
